<!-- ============ 06 BASE GRAPH ============ -->
<div class="wrap">
  <section id="base">
    <div class="seg rv"><span class="num">06</span><span class="kicker">The vision</span></div>
    <h2 class="rv">Every organization shares a skeleton. <em>Name it once.</em></h2>
    <p class="lede rv d1"><strong>The method is how we work. The base graph is what we start <em style="font-style:italic;color:var(--ink)">from</em>.</strong> Strip away the specifics and every org graph is built from the same parts: people, departments, processes, systems, metrics, friction, risk, opportunity. That shared skeleton can be crystallized into a base graph — <span class="hl-work">Organization.aDNA</span> (an organization's agentic DNA) — that you fork and specialize for each new client. The structure is constant; only the contents change.</p>

    <!-- D6: base -> instances -->
    <div class="rv d2" style="margin:30px 0 10px">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 1160 260" width="100%" fill="none" aria-label="A base Organization.aDNA graph forks down into specialized client instances.">
        <!-- base -->
        <g transform="translate(470,20)">
