        </g>
        <text x="600" y="146" fill="#6d6962" font-family="'JetBrains Mono Variable', monospace" font-size="10">fork &amp; specialize ↓</text>
        <!-- instances -->
        <g font-family="Inter, sans-serif">
          <g transform="translate(130,180)"><rect width="200" height="56" rx="11" fill="rgba(169,143,224,0.07)" stroke="rgba(169,143,224,0.4)"/><text x="100" y="26" text-anchor="middle" fill="#ece8e1" font-size="14" font-weight="600">Client A</text><text x="100" y="44" text-anchor="middle" fill="#a8a39b" font-family="'JetBrains Mono Variable', monospace" font-size="10">+ its own people, tools, seams</text></g>
          <g transform="translate(480,180)"><rect width="200" height="56" rx="11" fill="rgba(169,143,224,0.07)" stroke="rgba(169,143,224,0.4)"/><text x="100" y="26" text-anchor="middle" fill="#ece8e1" font-size="14" font-weight="600">Client B</text><text x="100" y="44" text-anchor="middle" fill="#a8a39b" font-family="'JetBrains Mono Variable', monospace" font-size="10">same skeleton, new contents</text></g>
          <g transform="translate(830,180)"><rect width="200" height="56" rx="11" fill="rgba(169,143,224,0.07)" stroke="rgba(169,143,224,0.4)"/><text x="100" y="26" text-anchor="middle" fill="#ece8e1" font-size="14" font-weight="600">Client C</text><text x="100" y="44" text-anchor="middle" fill="#a8a39b" font-family="'JetBrains Mono Variable', monospace" font-size="10">specialized in days, not weeks</text></g>
        </g>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <p class="rv d1" style="margin-top:6px">The same shape points three directions — and the base graph serves all of them:</p>
    <div class="dirs rv d2">
      <div class="dir"><div class="da">Inside-out</div><b>Run on your own graph</b><p>An organization governs and operates itself through its living context graph.</p></div>
      <div class="dir is-this"><div class="da">Outside-in · this</div><b>Model an organization</b><p>We build a graph of a company as a subject — exactly what the engagement does.</p></div>
      <div class="dir"><div class="da">Aggregating-in</div><b>A network of orgs</b><p>Many organizations roll up into one live, federated picture.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="callout rv d2">
      <div class="lbl">Why it scales</div>
      <p>You never start from a blank page. You fork a base that already knows what an organization <em style="font-style:italic;color:var(--ink)">is</em> — the node types, the tag discipline, the engines — and you fill it in. The expensive part is built once.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>

<!-- ============ 07 BUILD OPERATE ACCESS ============ -->
<div class="wrap">
  <section id="boa">
    <div class="seg rv"><span class="num">07</span><span class="kicker">The opportunity</span></div>
    <h2 class="rv">Today this runs on agents and operators. It's waiting for a <em>front end</em>.</h2>
    <p class="lede rv d1">Right now, building, operating, and accessing one of these graphs happens through files, structured documents, and an agent doing disciplined work. That's the proof it works. The unlock is a front end that puts all three in anyone's hands.</p>

    <div class="boa" style="margin-top:30px">
      <div class="panel-boa build rv d1">
        <svg class="bi" viewBox="0 0 40 40" fill="none"><rect x="6" y="6" width="12" height="12" rx="2" stroke="#bb9af7" stroke-width="1.6"/><rect x="22" y="6" width="12" height="12" rx="2" stroke="#bb9af7" stroke-width="1.6"/><rect x="14" y="22" width="12" height="12" rx="2" stroke="#bb9af7" stroke-width="1.6"/><path d="M12 18 L 20 22 M28 18 L 20 22" stroke="#bb9af7" stroke-width="1.4"/></svg>
        <div class="verb">Build</div>
        <p>Guided discovery, graph construction, and validation — turn interviews and documents into a structured, sourced model without needing an agent to hand-author every node.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:11px;color:var(--ink-faint);font-style:italic;font-size:13.5px">Picture a canvas where a transcript drops in and becomes sourced, taggable nodes you accept or correct.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="panel-boa operate rv d2">
        <svg class="bi" viewBox="0 0 40 40" fill="none"><path d="M20 6 a14 14 0 1 1 -10 4" stroke="#f2cd83" stroke-width="1.6" fill="none"/><path d="M10 6 v8 h8" stroke="#f2cd83" stroke-width="1.6" fill="none"/><circle cx="20" cy="20" r="3" fill="#f2cd83"/></svg>
        <div class="verb">Operate</div>
        <p>Keep the graph alive — re-validate as things change, track what moved and when, and run the enablement ladder from crawl to walk to agent-native.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:11px;color:var(--ink-faint);font-style:italic;font-size:13.5px">Picture a dashboard that flags what's gone stale and walks a team up the adoption ladder.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="panel-boa access rv d3">
        <svg class="bi" viewBox="0 0 40 40" fill="none"><circle cx="17" cy="17" r="10" stroke="#7dcfff" stroke-width="1.6"/><path d="M24 24 L 33 33" stroke="#7dcfff" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round"/><path d="M12 17 h10 M17 12 v10" stroke="#7dcfff" stroke-width="1.3"/></svg>
        <div class="verb">Access</div>
        <p>Query it, project a safe view for any audience, generate board-ready reports on demand, and surface the next opportunity — from one source of truth.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:11px;color:var(--ink-faint);font-style:italic;font-size:13.5px">Picture a query bar that answers &ldquo;where's our biggest manual-work cost?&rdquo; — and exports the deck.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="rv d1" style="margin-top:30px"><strong>Why now —</strong> agents are finally good enough to act on a structured model of a company, but only if one exists. The method that produces it is proven and the engines are real. The interface is the missing layer.</p>
    <p class="rv d1"><strong>The opening —</strong> today this ships as bespoke engagement work: expensive, and one company at a time. A front end turns that service into a product — the same graph, built, operated, and accessed by anyone, at software margins. Whoever builds it owns the layer between every organization and the AI meant to help it.</p>
    <div class="callout rv d2" style="margin-top:26px">
      <div class="lbl">The shape of it</div>
      <p><strong>The method is proven and the engines are real.</strong> What's missing is the surface that lets anyone build, operate, and access a graph without an operator in the loop. That interface is the product still to build — and it sits on top of everything on this page.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>

